Quarter the @Closed Cup Mushrooms{150%g}. Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces. Zest then halve the @Lime{1/2}. Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}. Bash the @Lemongrass{1} stick with a #saucepan{} to release the flavours.

Heat a splash of oil in a #large saucepan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the mushrooms, pepper and lemongrass. Stir and cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @Ginger Puree{1/2%tsp} and @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Add less spice if you don't like too much heat.

Pour in the @Coconut Milk{200%ml} and bring to a simmer. Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Sauce{300%ml} along with the @Peanut Butter{1%tbsp}. Simmer until the veggies are soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Unsalted Roasted Peanuts{25%g}.

When the veggies are soft, stir in the @Egg Noodle Nest{2}. Make sure they are submerged in the laksa. Simmer until tender, about ~{4%minutes}.

> TIP: The noodles may soak up some of the coconutty liquid. If this is the case, just add a splash of water to get it back to a soupy consistency.

Remove and discard the lemongrass. Stir in the @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and lime zest, then add lime juice and @salt{} to taste. Share between your #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkle of peanuts and spring onion. Enjoy!

> MOD: If you've added @?King Prawns{150%g} to your meal, add them to the pan when you add the noodles and cook for the same amount of time.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.